title: X Factor 2015: People are pretty impressed with two of Rita Ora's final three girls
text:
X Factor 2015: People are pretty impressed with two of Rita Ora's final three girls X Factor 2015: People are pretty impressed with two of Rita Ora's final three girls 
Press Association 2014 / / National Entertainment News Share 
So it was another tough day for Rita Ora, as she made that agonising decision to halve the numbers in the Girls category to take through to the X Factor live shows. 
With Meghan Trainor right beside her at a gorgeous, sunny mansion in Los Angeles to help her out, Rita managed to pick her final three. Oh my god. Decision time. I feel sick. What shall I do guys? #XFactor 
— Rita Ora (@RitaOra) October 25, 2015 
“I am going to go with the three who have the potential to entertain live on every single week,” Rita told hosts Caroline Flack and Olly Murs. 
Louisa Johnson was the first to get through. Louisa Johnson (Thames/Syco) 
The 17-year-old couldn’t contain her excitement when her name was announced. But did Rita make the right choice? 
Twitter certainly thought so.
